commit.message: fbpdf.1: update and improve the manual page
poppler: return NULL from doc_open() if malloc() fails
draw: read FBDEV environment variable
fbpdf: more accurate mark vertical position after recent changes

mupdf: allow zoom levels that are not a multiple of 10

Based on a patch by Nicolas Caramelli.

Avoid passing non-constant format string to printf

gcc complains loudly on any code that uses anything but string literal
as format string to printf. Right now format string is "const char *"
and does not contain %-sequences, but should '%' appear in "usage"
string in future, bad things would happen.

Since formatting functionality of "printf" is not used anyway, replacing
it with "puts" makes code both safer and easier to understand.
fbpdf.1: write a man page

fbpdf: add keybinding to invert colors

Pressing "I" in fbpdf will now invert the colors of the open
document.
mupdf: support for mupdf-1.14
fbpdf: switch to ISC
mupdf: support mupdf-1.10
fbpdf: include termios.h instead of pty.h

fbpdf: prefer CTRLKEY() to glibc's CTRL() macro

Reported by Christian Neukirchen <chneukirchen@gmail.com>.
mupdf: support mupdf-1.7

LICENSE: include the modified bsd

Debian seems to require this.
Suggested by Dmitry Bogatov <KAction@gnu.org>.
fbpdf: update the vertical position only if loadpage() succeeds
fbpdf: do not free page buffer in reload()
README: reword the introduction
fbpdf: fix jumping to previous position mark
fbpdf: allocate page buffer when rendering

fbpdf: zero-page documents are broken

The problem is fz_open_document() may not fail for broken
pdf files, which is unacceptable.
poppler: crop the rendered page if it is too large
fbpdf: show a message and exit if redrawing fails
mupdf: return NULL if doc_open() fails
fbpdf: C centers the page horizontally

fbpdf: O command sets page number and shows current page

For instance, the command '3O' in page 5 of a file:
1. Updates current page number so that the command 'nG'
   shows page n + 2, where n is the prefix (just like the
   command '3o').
2. Invokes command G with current page as its prefix, i.e.,
   '5G', which shows page 7.

mupdf: support mupdf-1.4

It seems libmupdf now depends on -lmujs and openssl's -lcrypto
(the latter can be disabled by editing mupdf's Makerules).

poppler: include draw.h

Reported by Konstantinn Bonnet <qu7uux@gmail.com>.
fbpdf: add Z command to change the default zoom level
djvulibre: support rotation
